n','4'),(185,2,'Which of the following is server side programming languages?<br/><br/>1.HTML<br/>2.JavaScript<br/>3.JSP<br/>4.Sevlets','1,2,3,4','1,2','3,4','None of these','3'),(186,2,'Which of the following JSP variables are not available within a JSP expression. Select the one correct answer.','session','request','response','httpsession','4'),(187,2,'Which of these are legal attributes of page directive.','include','scopePage','errorPage','debug','3'),(188,2,'Which of these are true. Select the two correct answers.','The default value of isThreadSafe attribute of page directive is true.','If isThreadSafe attribute of page directive is set to true, then JSP container dispatches request for the page sequentially','Setting isThreadSage attribute to true for JSP pages, can lead to poor performance.','All of these','1'),(189,2,'Which of these is true about include directive. Select the one correct answer.','The included file must have jspf extension.','The XML syntax of include directive in &lt;jsp:include file=\"fileName\"/&gt;.','The content of file included using include directive, cannot refer to variables local to the original page.','When using the include directive, the JSP container treats the file to be included as if it was part of the original file.','4'),(190,2,'Which statements is incorrect?','HttpServlet.service() thrwos ServletException and IOException','HttpServlet.init() throws ServletException','HttpServlet.destroy() throws ServletException','All of these','3'),(191,2,'What JSTL stands for?','JavaServer Pages Standard Tag Library','JSP Tag Library','Java Standard Tag Library','None of these.','1'),(192,2,'Following is not a implicit object?','request','response','cookie','session','3'),(193,2,'application is object of which class?','javax.servlet.ServletContext','javax.servlet.HttpContext','javax.servlet.Context','javax.servlet.Application','1'),(194,2,'config is object of which class?','javax.servlet.ServletContext','javax.servlet.ServletConfig','ja